== 制作和宣传 ==
《巴格达地毯》改编自哈罗德·麦克格拉斯（{{lang|en|Harold MacGrath}}）1911年的同名小说<ref name="Variety11">{{cite journal | title = The Carpet from Bagdad | journal = Variety | volume = 38 | issue = 11 | date = 1915-05-14 | page = 19 | url = https://archive.org/stream/variety38-1915-05#page/n54/mode/1up | accessdate = 2015-03-12}}</ref>。麦克格拉斯是见多识广的作家，有十余部成功的小说作品<ref name="BNS">{{cite journal | title = Harold MacGrath | journal = The Bookseller, Newsdealer, and Stationer | volume = 38 | issue = 11 | date = 1913-06-01 | page = 496}}</ref>。当时以[[亚洲|亚洲]]为背景的故事比较流行<ref name="PW">{{cite journal | title = The Literary Invasion of Asia | journal = The Publishers' Weekly | volume = 80 | issue = 15 | date = 1911-10-07 | pages = 1409–1410}}</ref>，制作本片的{{lang|en|Selig Polyscope}}公司之前还制作了另一个系列的麦克格拉斯小说改编电影《[[凯思琳历险记|凯思琳历险记]]》（{{lang|en|''The Adventures of Kathlyn''}}）。与《巴格达地毯》一样，这个非常成功的系列也有[[近东|近东]]的故事背景。<ref name="MPN63">{{cite journal | author = Milne P. | title = The Carpet from Bagdad | journal = Motion Picture News | volume = 11 | issue = 19 | page = 63 | date = 1915-05-15 | accessdate = 2015-03-12 | url = https://archive.org/stream/motionpicturenew112unse#page/n658/mode/1up}}</ref>

[[导演|导演]]科林·坎贝尔（{{lang|en|Colin Campbell}}）非常看重电影的真实感，他要求剧组搭建多条街道的外景，分别代表开罗、[[巴格达|巴格达]]和大马士革<ref name="Moto686">{{cite journal | title = Selig's First Spectacular Special | journal = Motography | volume = 13 | issue = 18 | date = 1915-05-01 | page = 686 | url = https://archive.org/stream/motography13elec#page/686/mode/1up | accessdate = 2015-03-12}}</ref>，还动用了塞利格动物园的多种动物<ref name="Variety11" />。以[[阿拉伯|阿拉伯]]地区和[[撒哈拉沙漠|撒哈拉沙漠]]为背景的镜头实际上是在[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的沙漠中拍摄<ref name="Moto686" /><ref name="Williams">{{cite journal | author = Williams K. | title = Kathlyn Williams' Experiences in a Desert Sand Storm and How She Learned to Ride a Camel | journal = Bismarck Daily Tribune | location = Bismarck, North Dakota | volume = 35 | issue = 133 | date = 1915-06-04 | edition = Last | page = 6 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131112171704/http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042242/1915-06-04/ed-1/seq-6/ | url = http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042242/1915-06-04/ed-1/seq-6/ | archivedate = 2013-11-12}}</ref>。

片中的阿拉伯人物所穿的是真正的阿拉伯服装，电影在沙漠拍摄期间，扮演这些角色的演员需要一直穿着这些进口服装，以求他们在镜头前的表现能够更加自然<ref name="Williams" />。电影包括沙漠场景在内的大部分镜头胶片都是[[电影上色|手工着色]]<ref name="Moto779">{{cite journal | author = Caine CJ. | title = Selig's "The Carpet from Bagdad" | journal = Motography | volume = 13 | issue = 19 | date = 1915-05-15 | page = 779 | accessdate = 2015-03-12 | url = https://archive.org/stream/motography13elec#page/779/mode/1up}}</ref>。影片制作耗资超过3万5000美元<ref name="UTTT">{{cite journal | title = Playhouse Paragraphs | journal = Up-to-the-Times Magazine | volume = 10 | issue = 3 | date = 1916-01 | page = 5882 | url = http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433081655809;view=1up;seq=162 | accessdate = 2015-03-12 | archive-date = 2013-12-02 | archive-url = https://archive.is/20131202164429/http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433081655809;view=1up;seq=162 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，相当于如今的至少{{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|35000|1915|r=-5}}}}美元{{Inflation-fn|US}}。

[[威廉·尼古拉斯·塞利格|威廉·塞利格]]（{{lang|en|William Selig}}）积极地为自己的{{lang|en|Selig Polyscope}}制片公司及旗下电影作宣传。1915年3月，媒体获许参观尚未建成的塞利格动物园，[[记者|记者]]能够在现场看到《巴格达地毯》的集市外景。<ref name="Afra">{{cite journal | title = 'Seventeen Happy Days' in Hollywood: Selig Polyscope's Promotional Campaign for the Movie Special of July 1915 | author = Afra K. | journal = Film History | volume = 22 | issue = 2 | pages = 199–218 | year = 2010 | issn = 0892-2160 | doi = 10.2979/fil.2010.22.2.199}}</ref>{{lang|en|Selig Polyscope}}制片公司、[[维塔格拉夫制片厂|维塔格拉夫制片厂]]（{{lang|en|Vitagraph Studios}}）、[[鲁宾制造公司|鲁宾制造公司]]（{{lang|en|Lubin Manufacturing Company}}）和[[芝加哥埃森内工作室|芝加哥埃森内工作室]]（{{lang|en|Essanay Studios}}）共同组合集团公司“{{lang|en|V-L-S-E}}”<ref>{{cite book | author = Erish AA. | title = Col. William N. Selig, the Man Who Invented Hollywood | year = 2012 | publisher = University of Texas Press | isbn = 978-0-292-72870-7 | page = 198}}</ref>，本片正是新集团公司发行的第一部电影<ref>{{cite book | author = Slide A. | title = The New Historical Dictionary of the American Film Industry | publisher = Routledge | year = 1998 | page = 224 | isbn = 978-1-57958-056-8}}</ref>。麦克格拉斯原著小说出版商鲍勃斯梅里尔公司（{{lang|en|Bobbs-Merrill Company}}）在旗下美术画廊试映本片，只有获得邀请的人士才能入场。这也成为电影长片经赞助商资助，在剧院以外的地方试映的早期范例。<ref>{{cite book | author = Waller GA. | editor = Christie I. | title = Audiences | chapter = Locating Early Non-Theatrical Audiences | year = 2012 | publisher = Amsterdam University Press | series = The Key Debates | isbn = 978-90-8964-362-9 | page = 91}}</ref>

== 反响和影响 ==
[[File:Carpetfrombagdad_with_carpet.JPG|thumb]]

《巴格达地毯》于1915年5月3日发行<ref name="AFI" />，获得评论界的普遍好评。《[[综艺_(杂志)|综艺]]》刊文称，影片的内容比片名所能够隐含的信息更为丰富有趣，无论“导演和表演都无懈可击”<ref name="Variety11" />。《电影新闻报》（{{lang|en|''Motion Picture News''}}）的彼得·米尔恩（{{lang|en|Peter Milne}}）称赞坎贝尔对细节和真实性的着重把握<ref name="MPN63" />。詹姆斯·麦奎德（{{lang|en|James McQuade}}）在《电影世界》（{{lang|en|''The Moving Picture World''}}）上赞扬本片的演员表演和特技效果，但他认为小说中有一处发生在开罗的细节，可以让读者更容易理解穆罕默德的行为动机，但电影中没有包含这一细节，在他看来，《巴格达地毯》即便是与坎贝尔1914年推出的《[[破坏者_(1914年电影)|破坏者]]》（{{lang|en|''The Spoilers''}}）相比也只“略逊半筹”<ref name="TMPW198">{{cite journal | author = McQuade JS. | title = The Carpet from Bagdad | journal = The Moving Picture World | volume = 23 | issue = 2 | date = 1915-01-09 | page = 198 | accessdate = 2015-03-12 | url = https://archive.org/stream/movingpicturewor23newy#page/198/mode/1up}}</ref>。《影像杂志》（{{lang|en|''Motography''}}）的克拉伦斯·凯恩（{{lang|en|Clarence Caine}}）也认为，《巴格达地毯》与《破坏者》相比毫不逊色，他认为本片最出色的方面在于色彩，特别是片尾的沙漠日落镜头<ref name="Moto779" />。还有多份报纸评论对沙漠镜头的上色赞不绝口<ref name="Mildura">{{cite journal | title = Olympia Pictures | journal = The Mildura Cultivator | location = Mildura, Australia | date = 1916-03-08 | issue = 1788 | page = 11 | accessdate = 2015-03-12 | url = http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/page/7111658?zoomLevel=3 | archive-date = 2015-11-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151128065157/http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/page/7111658?zoomLevel=3 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Feilding">{{cite journal | title = "The Carpet from Bagdad" at the Lyceum | journal = The Feilding Star | location = Feilding, New Zealand | volume = 12 | issue = 2920 | date = 1916-04-18 | page = 3 | accessdate = 2015-03-13 | url = http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=FS19160418.1.3&e=-------10--1----0-- | archive-date = 2016-03-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305135809/http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d | dead-url = no }}</ref>，[[新西兰|新西兰]]的《莱文纪事报》（{{lang|en|''The Levin Chronicle''}}）甚至称赞电影对色彩的使用堪称“摄影师的艺术瑰宝”<ref name="Horowhenua">{{cite journal | title = The Carpet from Bagdad | journal = The Levin Chronicle | location = Levin, New Zealand | date = 1918-02-14 | page = 3 | accessdate = 2015-03-13 | url = http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=HC19180214.1.3&e=-------10--1----0-- | archive-date = 2016-03-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305135809/http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d | dead-url = no }}</ref>。不过，基蒂·凯利（{{lang|en|Kitty Kelly}}）发表在《[[芝加哥論壇報|芝加哥論壇報]]》上的评论看法更为复杂，她认为电影中的风景过于出色，导致观众对人物的刻画关注不够，同时凯瑟琳·威廉姆斯这时已经35岁，再来出演纯真少女实在缺乏说服力。<ref name="CDT">{{cite journal | title = Flickerings from Film Land | author = Kelly K. | journal = Chicago Daily Tribune | date = 1915-05-12 | page = 16 | accessdate = 2015-03-13 | url = http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1915/01/06/page/10/article/flickerings-from-film-land/ | archive-date = 2015-04-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402154843/http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1915/01/06/page/10/article/flickerings-from-film-land/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

虽然电影获得许多同时代评论家的好评，但[[英国电影协会|英国电影协会]]的克莱德·吉文斯（{{lang|en|Clyde Jeavons}}）认为，研究默片时代的现代学者不会将《巴格达地毯》视为杰作<ref name="Jeavons">{{cite journal | author = Jeavons C. | title = Sunken treasure: The 'Lusitania' yields an archaeological curiosity | journal = Sight & Sound | volume = 52 | issue = 1 | year = Winter 1982–1983 | page = 4}}</ref>。

=== 部分再发现 ===
与默片时代的大部分电影一样，《巴格达地毯》在很长时间里都只是一部完全失传的电影。但到了1982年，[[国际海洋工程公司|国际海洋工程公司]]的潜水打捞探险队从[[卢西塔尼亚号|卢西塔尼亚号]]残骸中打捞出多件文物，其中就有本片的一卷胶片。<ref>{{cite book | author = Diana Preston | title = Lusitania: An Epic Tragedy | accessdate = 2015-03-13 | page = 374 | isbn = 978-0-8027-1375-9 | year = 2002 | url = http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Lusitania.html?id=cIkv-mteIEAC | publisher = Walker Publishing | archive-date = 2015-04-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402105035/http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Lusitania.html?id=cIkv-mteIEAC | dead-url = no }}</ref>在[[英国广播公司|英国广播公司]][[技术顾问|技术顾问]]劳里·沃德（{{lang|en|Laurie Ward}}）的协助下，[[英国电影协会国家档案馆|英国电影协会国家档案馆]]成功复原数英尺胶片图像，从中可以辨别片名，但还无法达成任何程度的放映<ref name="Jeavons" />。卢西塔尼亚号上有电影院，船上装有多部电影的放映胶卷，这些胶卷都带到[[伦敦|伦敦]]供电影发行商预览，《巴格达地毯》的胶卷很可能也在其中，所以本片至今仍属佚失电影<ref>{{cite book | author = Bottomore S. | title = The Titanic and Silent Cinema | publisher = The Projection Box | accessdate = 2015-03-13 | url = http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=2KGJJsUggtAC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | year = 2000 | isbn = 978-1-903000-00-7 | page = 157 | archive-date = 2015-04-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402103421/http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=2KGJJsUggtAC&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

